Your request history is associated with a random, device-generated identifier for six months. Your request history may include transcripts, audio for users who have opted in to Improve Siri and Dictation, and related request data, such as device specifications, performance statistics, and the approximate location of your device at the time the request was made. After six months, your request history is dissociated from the random identifier and may be retained for up to two years to help Apple develop and improve Siri, Dictation, and other language processing features like Voice Control. The small subset of requests that have been reviewed may be kept beyond two years, without the random identifier, for ongoing improvement of Siri.

If one of your Siri or Dictation interactions is selected for review, the request, as well as the response Siri provided, will be analyzed to determine accuracy and to generally improve Siri, Dictation, and natural language processing functionality in Apple products and services. Depending on the context of your request, Apple employees may review Siri Data directly relevant to the request, in order to grade the effectiveness of Siri's response. Only Apple employees, subject to strict confidentiality obligations, are able to access audio interactions with Siri and Dictation. You can choose to disable Improve Siri and Dictation at any time. To do so, open the Home app on your iOS device that is signed into the same Apple ID as your HomePod, press and hold on the HomePod, tap Settings icon, then tap on “Analytics &amp; Improvement”, and turn off “Improve Siri &amp; Dictation.”

The preference selected when you set up or upgrade the operating system on an iPhone or iPad will apply to any connected Apple Watch or HomePod. You can control this preference for each device individually in Settings. 

You can delete audio interactions associated with a random identifier and retained for six months or less by opening the Home app on your iOS device, pressing on the HomePod, tapping Settings icon, then tapping “Siri History” and choosing “Delete Siri History.” 

By enabling Improve Siri and Dictation, you agree and consent to Apple’s and its subsidiaries’ and agents’ transmission, collection, maintenance, processing, and use of this information, including your audio interactions and Siri Data, to provide and improve Siri, Dictation, and other language processing features like Voice Control. At all times information received by Apple from your use of Siri or Dictation will be treated in accordance with Apple’s Privacy Policy, which can be found at www.apple.com/privacy.</base>
        <tran loc="zh-TW">若您選擇參與「改進Siri和聽寫」，則會允許Apple儲存並讓其員工檢閱您與Siri和聽寫互動時的音訊取樣，以協助開發和改進Siri、聽寫以及Apple產品和服務中的自然語言處理功能。除了錄音內容，其他Siri資料，如電腦對於您的要求所產生的聽寫記錄、您的聯絡人姓名、您裝置上安裝的App以及您的位置也會用來改進Siri。

您的要求記錄會與裝置產生的隨機識別碼產生關聯，時間為期六個月。您的要求記錄可能包含聽寫記錄、選擇參與「改進Siri和聽寫」的使用者音訊，以及相關的要求資料，如裝置規格、效能統計資料和您提出要求時的裝置大略位置。六個月之後，您的要求記錄即不會再與隨機識別碼有所關聯，且可能會保留最多兩年的時間，以協助Apple開發和改進Siri、聽寫和其他如「語音控制」的語言處理功能。

若您其中一項與Siri或聽寫的互動被選擇進行檢閱，您的要求以及Siri提供的回應都會進行分析，以確認其準確性並且整體改進Siri、聽寫以及Apple產品和服務中的自然語言處理功能。視您的要求內容而定，Apple的員工可能會檢閱與要求直接相關的Siri資料，以評定Siri回應的有效程度。只有遵守嚴格保密義務的Apple員工才能取用與Siri和聽寫的互動音訊。您可以隨時選擇停用「改進Siri和聽寫」。若要停用，請在已登入與HomePod相同Apple ID的iOS裝置上打開「家庭」App，在HomePod上按住，點一下「設定」圖像，然後點一下「分析與改進項目」並且關閉「改進Siri與聽寫」。

當您設定或升級iPhone或iPad的作業系統時，您所選擇的偏好設定也會套用到任何相關的Apple Watch或HomePod上。您可以在「設定」中單獨控制每部裝置的這項偏好設定。

您可以在iOS裝置上打開「家庭」App，在HomePod上按住，點一下「設定」圖像，然後點一下「Siri記錄」並選擇「刪除Siri記錄」來刪除與隨機識別碼相關且保留六個月或較短時間的音訊互動。

啟用「改進Siri和聽寫」即表示您同意並接受Apple及其子公司和代理傳送、收集、維護、處理和使用此資訊，包含您的音訊互動內容和Siri資料，以提供和改進Siri、聽寫和其他如「語音控制」的語言處理功能。在任何時間，Apple都會依照「Apple隱私權政策」的規定來處理從您使用Siri或聽寫時所接收到的資訊，請參訪：www.apple.com/tw/privacy</tran>
