    <TextItem>
      <Description/>
      <Position>FOOTER_TEXT_WIFI_IPOD</Position>
      <TranslationSet>
        <base loc="en">iOS Device Analytics

iPod Analytics may include details about hardware and operating system specifications, performance statistics, and data about how you use your devices and applications. None of the collected information identifies you personally. Personal data is either not logged at all, is subject to privacy preserving techniques such as differential privacy, or is removed from any reports before they’re sent to Apple. You can review this information on your iOS device by going to Settings &gt; Privacy &gt; Analytics and looking under Analytics Data.

If you have consented to provide Apple with this information, and you have Location Services turned on, the location of your devices may also be sent to help Apple analyze performance issues (for example, the strength or weakness of a mobile or Wi-Fi signal in a particular location). This analytics location data may include locations such as the location of your devices once per day, the location where a call ends, or the location of a failed in-store transaction. You may choose to turn off Location Services for Analytics at any time. To do so, go to Settings &gt; Privacy &gt; Location Services &gt; System Services and turn off the iPod Analytics switch.

If you agree to send Analytics information to Apple from multiple devices that use the same iCloud account, we may correlate some usage data about Apple apps across those devices by syncing using end-to-end encryption. We do this in a manner that does not identify you to Apple.

You may also choose to turn off Device Analytics altogether. To do so, go to Settings &gt; Privacy &gt; Analytics, and set “Share iPod touch Analytics” to off.

By using these features, you agree and consent to Apple’s and its subsidiaries’ and agents’ transmission, collection, maintenance, processing, and use of this information as described above.

At all times, information received by Apple will be treated in accordance with Apple’s Privacy Policy, which can be found at www.apple.com/privacy</base>
        <tran loc="zh-TW">iOS裝置分析

「iPod分析」可能包含硬體和作業系統規格的詳細資訊、執行效能的統計資料、您如何使用裝置與應用程式的資料等。收集的資訊皆無法識別您的個人身分。個人資料不是未在記錄範圍內，受到隱私權保護技術（如差分隱私）的規範，就是已在報告傳送給Apple 前移除。您可以前往iOS裝置上的「設定」&gt;「隱私權」&gt;「分析」，然後在「分析資料」下檢視此資訊。

若同意提供Apple此資訊，且已開啟「定位服務」，可能也會將您裝置的位置傳送給Apple來協助分析執行效能問題（例如，在某特定位置行動或Wi-Fi訊號的強弱）。此分析位置資料可能包含的位置有每天一次的裝置位置，通話結束的位置，或無法進行交易的商店位置等。您隨時都可以關閉「分析」功能的「定位服務」，若要關閉此服務，請前往「設定」&gt;「隱私權」&gt;「定位服務」&gt;「系統服務」，然後關閉「iPod分析」的開關。

若您同意從多部使用相同iCloud帳號的裝置傳送「分析」資訊給Apple，我們可能會藉由端對端加密同步來關聯每台裝置上Apple App的部分使用狀況資料。此做法並不會讓Apple識別您。

您也可以選擇關閉「裝置分析」功能，若要關閉此功能，請前往「設定」&gt;「隱私權」&gt;「分析」，然後關閉「分享iPod touch分析」的開關。

使用這些功能，即表示同意並接受Apple及其夥伴和被許可人以如上所示的方式傳播、收集、維護、處理和使用此資訊。

在任何時間，Apple都會依照「Apple隱私權政策」的規定來處理接收到的資訊，請參訪：www.apple.com/tw/privacy</tran>
      </TranslationSet>
