      <TranslationSet>
        <base loc="en">Providing the Stores

We use your personal information to provide the services and features in the Stores. This information includes, for example, your account and payment information, which you can access and change in settings, and your purchase history.

When you download from a Store, or install an app on your Apple Watch, identifiers such as your device’s hardware ID and IP address are logged by Apple along with your Apple ID.


Improving the Stores

To improve the experience in the Stores, we collect information about your usage of the Stores, including when you open or close a Store, what content you search for, and the content you view and download. We also collect information about your device such as the type of device, the version of your operating system, and the amount of free space on your device. We may use this information to assess whether requested content can be downloaded, to understand general trends in use of device storage, and whether your device is connected by Wi-Fi or cellular. We can use this information to improve your experience in the Stores in the following ways: 
 
User search data makes it possible for us to offer trending searches

Knowing what content you viewed or download makes it possible for us to offer personalized features like “More Games You Might Like”

Knowing the free space on your device allowed us to build the feature that lets you buy movies on your iPhone without downloading it at purchase

Additionally, if you have Popular Near Me enabled in Location Services, your iPhone will periodically send locations of when and where you have purchased or used apps in an anonymous and encrypted form to Apple, and may then be used to offer geographically relevant apps and other Apple products and services.

Personalizing the Stores

We use your interactions with the Stores to help you discover the content that’s most relevant to you. For example, we recommend content that we think will be of interest to you based on what you’ve previously searched for, viewed, downloaded, updated, or reviewed in the Stores. We also use your purchase history and payment methods together with account information derived from your Apple ID. To make better recommendations, we also use aggregate information about app launches, installs, and deletions from users who choose to share device analytics with Apple. Personalization features can be disabled by sliding off the Personalized Recommendations switch for your Apple ID in the iTunes &amp; App Store Settings. 

Advertising

Search Ads is an easy way for developers to promote their apps within App Store search results, helping people discover apps. We use information about your device, account, purchases, downloads and search terms in the App Store in order to ensure that ads in the Stores are relevant. We create groups of people, called segments, who share similar characteristics and we use these groups for delivering targeted ads. Information about you is used to determine which segments you are assigned to, and thus, which ads you receive. To protect your privacy, your information is used to place you into segments of at least 5,000 people. If you do not wish to receive ads targeted to your interests from Apple’s advertising platform, you can choose to enable Limit Ad Tracking, which will opt your Apple ID out of receiving such ads on devices where you are signed in with the same Apple ID.

We also use similar information from the Stores to make ads in Apple News more relevant, but in a way that is tied to an identifier specific to Apple News and not tied to your Apple ID. 

Learn more About Advertising &amp; Privacy in Search Ads and News here: https://support.apple.com/HT205223

Learn about how to opt out of interest-based ads in the App Store and Apple News here: https://support.apple.com/HT202074

If you choose to limit ad tracking, you will still receive ads based on search terms you enter.

Sharing with third parties

We are obligated to provide some non-personal information about your content purchases to strategic partners, such as app developers and/or content owners so that they can measure the performance of their creative work, meet royalty and accounting requirements, and improve their products and services.

We may share information with developers to help them operate and improve their apps. Developers can access usage information, provided by users who opt in, that allows them to look at aggregated data from groups of users that have similar characteristics or behavior, as long the data comes from groups of no less than five users. Developers can access receipt information for purchases of their products and services in the Stores. Receipts do not include personal information; however, developers could seek to associate them with personal information from your use and download of their apps, if you have provided it to them.

If you purchase a subscription in a third-party app, we create a Subscriber ID that is unique to you and the developer or publisher. You can learn more about Subscriber ID here: https://support.apple.com/HT207233

Retention

We retain personal information associated with your purchases and downloads on our Stores for the periods specified by applicable laws relating to financial reporting which vary by country. For most customers that requires at least a ten year retention period. We also retain a record of your purchase and downloads of content for at least as long as you have an account with us to allow you to download that content again in line with our applicable terms. We retain other information such as browsing activity and searches for a shorter period. The period chosen takes account of applicable legal requirements to retain data and specific business use cases. However, some information, such as purchases, but not your stored card details may be retained as business records even after you close your account or stop using the Stores.

Preventing fraud and other malicious activity

We also collect personal information to prevent fraud and other malicious activity in the Stores and other Apple apps and services. This information includes device information, such as device type and software version, location information, if available, download and purchase history, and other interactions with the Stores.

We also compute a device trust score on your device when you attempt a purchase using information about how you use your device, including the approximate number of phone calls or emails you send and receive. The submission is designed so Apple cannot learn the underlying values on your device. The score is stored for a fixed time on our servers.

At all times, information collected by Apple will be treated in accordance with Apple’s Privacy Policy, which can be found at www.apple.com/privacy</base>
        <tran loc="zh-TW">提供商店內容

我們會使用您的個人資訊以在「商店」中提供服務與功能。此資訊包含如您的帳號和付款資訊（您可以在設定中取用並更改），以及您的購物記錄。

當您從「商店」下載，或在Apple Watch上安裝App時，Apple會記錄您的Apple ID連帶裝置硬體識別碼和IP位址等識別碼。


改進商店

為改進「商店」中的使用體驗，我們會收集您在「商店」中的使用狀況資訊，包含您何時打開或關閉「商店」，您搜尋的內容，以及您檢視和下載的內容。我們也會收集您的裝置資訊，例如裝置類型、作業系統版本，以及裝置的可用空間。我們可能會使用此資訊來評估要求的內容是否可供下載、瞭解裝置儲存空間平常的使用傾向，以及您的裝置是連接Wi-Fi或行動網路。我們可以利用此資訊來改進您在「商店」中的使用體驗，方法如下：

使用者的搜尋資料有助於我們提供流行趨勢的搜尋

瞭解您檢視或下載的內容有助於我們提供個人化的功能，如「更多您可能會喜歡的遊戲」

瞭解您裝置的可用空間可讓我們建立您在iPhone上購買影片時無須下載的功能

此外，若您在「定位服務」中啟用「附近的熱門應用程式」，您的iPhone將定期以匿名和加密的方式傳送您購買或使用App的時間與地點給Apple，且此資訊可能會用來提供地理相關的App和其他Apple產品和服務。

個人化商店

我們會使用您與「商店」的互動情況來協助您探索與您最相關的內容。例如，我們會依據您先前在「商店」中搜尋、檢視、下載、更新或觀看過的內容來建議您可能最感興趣的內容。我們也會使用您的購買記錄和付款方式連同來自Apple ID的帳號資訊。為提供更好的建議，我們也會使用關於App啟動、安裝和刪除的匯總資訊，這些資訊是來自選擇與Apple分享裝置分析資訊的使用者。您可在「iTunes與App Store設定」中滑動關閉Apple ID的「個人化推薦」開關以停用個人化功能。

廣告

「搜尋廣告」可讓開發者以簡單的方式在App Store搜尋結果中推廣他們的App，協助使用者探索App。我們會在App Store中使用您裝置、帳號、購買項目、下載項目和搜尋詞彙的相關資訊，以確保「商店」中的廣告具有相關性。我們會製作有相似特質的人員群組（稱為分類），並使用這些群組傳送定向廣告。您的個人資訊會用來決定您是屬於哪一個分類，您會因此收到相關的廣告。為了保護您的隱私權，您的個人資訊會用來將您分配到至少擁有5,000名人員的分類中。若您不想收到Apple廣告平台依據您的興趣所傳送的定向廣告，您可以選擇啟用「限制廣告追蹤」，在您以相同Apple ID登入的裝置上，Apple ID便不會接收到此類廣告。

我們也會使用類似的「商店」資訊來讓Apple News中的廣告更具相關性，但會綁定至Apple News特定的識別碼，而非您的Apple ID。

瞭解「搜尋廣告」和「新聞」的「關於廣告與隱私權」，網址如下：https://support.apple.com/zh-tw/HT205223

 瞭解如何選擇不接收App Store和Apple News中基於興趣的廣告，網址如下：https://support.apple.com/zh-tw/HT202074

 若您選擇限制廣告追蹤，您仍會收到基於所輸入搜尋詞彙的廣告。

與第三方分享

我們有義務將與內容購買項目相關的非個人資訊提供給策略合作夥伴，例如App開發者和/或內容擁有者，以便他們評估其創意作品的表現，滿足版稅及會計需求，並改善其產品與服務。

我們可能會與開發者分享資訊以協助他們作業和改進App。開發者可以取用由使用者選擇提供的使用狀況資訊，以便查看具有相似特質與行為的使用者群組的彙集資料，前提是資料所屬的群組人數不得少於五人。開發者可以接收「商店」中他們產品和服務的購買收據資訊。收據不包含個人資訊；不過，若您曾提供個人資訊，開發者可以從您的App使用和下載狀況來試圖與個人資訊取得關聯。

若您在第三方App中購買訂閱服務。我們會製作您與開發者或出版商而言為專屬的「訂閱者識別碼」。您可於以下網站深入瞭解「訂閱者識別碼」：https://support.apple.com/zh-tw/HT207233

 保留

我們會保留您在「商店」中與購買和下載內容相關的個人資訊一段時間，此保留時間視各國財務報告適用的相關法律而有所不同。針對大部分的消費者，需要至少十年的保留期。我們也會保留您的內容購買和下載記錄，保留期間至少為您擁有我們帳號的期間，以便您在符合適用條款的情況下可重新下載內容。我們會保留如瀏覽記錄和搜尋內容等其他資訊較短時間。所選的保留期間會考量到適用的法律需求以保留資料和特定業務使用案例。不過，即使您關閉帳號或停止使用「商店」，部分資訊（例如購買項目，而非您儲存的卡片詳細資訊）可能會依營業記錄需求留底。

防範詐騙和其他惡意活動

我們也會收集個人資訊以防範「商店」和其他Apple App與服務中的詐騙和其他惡意活動。此資訊包含裝置資訊，例如裝置類型和軟體版本、位置資訊（若有提供）、下載和購買記錄，以及其他在「商店」中的互動。

當您嘗試使用與裝置用途有關的資訊（包含您收發的通話或電子郵件的大約數量）來進行購物時，我們也會在裝置上計算裝置的信任分數。送出資訊的方式是經過設計的，Apple並無法得知您裝置上的真實數值。這些分數會儲存在我們的伺服器上一段固定的時間。

在任何時間，Apple都會依照「Apple隱私權政策」的規定來處理收集到的資訊，請參訪：www.apple.com/tw/privacy</tran>
      </TranslationSet>
