    <TextItem>
      <Description/>
      <Position>FOOTER_TEXT_WLAN</Position>
      <TranslationSet>
        <base loc="en">iMessage is an Apple service that sends messages over WLAN or cellular connections to other iOS devices (with iOS 5 or later), iPadOS devices, Mac computers (with OS X 10.8 or later), and Apple Watches. These messages don’t count against your messaging plan. Messages sent via iMessage can include photos, videos, and other information.

FaceTime is an Apple service that makes video or audio calls to someone who’s also using an iOS or iPadOS device or a Mac, or audio calls using an Apple Watch. These calls don’t count against your cellular minutes.

We designed iMessage and FaceTime to use end-to-end encryption, so there’s no way for Apple to decrypt the content of your conversations when they are in transit between devices. Attachments you send over iMessage (such as photos or videos) are encrypted so that no one but the sender and receiver(s) can access them. These encrypted attachments may be uploaded to Apple. To improve performance, your device may automatically upload attachments to Apple while you are composing an iMessage. If your message isn’t sent, the attachments are deleted from the server after 30 days. When a passcode or password is set on your iOS, iPadOS, or watchOS device, stored messages are encrypted on your device so that they can’t be accessed unless the device has been unlocked.

You can choose to automatically delete your iMessages from your device after 30 days or a year, or to keep them on your device forever. For your convenience, iMessages are backed up in iCloud and encrypted if you have either iCloud Backup or Messages in iCloud enabled. You can turn off both iCloud Backup and Messages in iCloud whenever you want. On iOS or iPadOS, go to Settings &gt; [your name] &gt; iCloud. On macOS, choose Messages &gt; Preferences, tap iMessage, and turn off “Enable Messages in iCloud.” We never store the content of FaceTime calls.

You can sign in to iMessage and FaceTime using your Apple ID, or just your phone number. If you sign in with your Apple ID on your device, you will be signed in to iMessage and FaceTime automatically. Your Apple ID or phone numbers will be shown to the people you contact, and people can reach you using your Apple ID, and email addresses or phone numbers on your account. You can select which phone numbers or email addresses you’d like to start new conversations from, and which phone numbers or email addresses you can receive messages and reply from, in iMessage and FaceTime settings. You can add and verify additional “Reachable At” information from your Apple ID account page.

Share Name and Photo allows you to share a name and photo with people you iMessage. You can choose to automatically share with just your contacts, or to be prompted each time. Your shared name and photo will be sent with your next iMessage to the people you share with, and stored on their devices. If you share your name and photo with an iMessage conversation with multiple people, your name and photo will be sent to all the people in the conversation. You can update your name and photo at any time. If you automatically share, updates will be sent when you next send an iMessage to each person you share with. If you have shared your name and photo and later turn off sharing, others who previously received your name and photo may still have your information on their devices. The name and photo you select for messages will be sent to Apple, and stored on Apple’s servers encrypted in a way that Apple cannot see.

Apple may record and store some information related to your use of iMessage and FaceTime to operate and improve Apple’s products and services:

• When you use iMessage and FaceTime, Apple may store information about your use of the services in a way that doesn’t identify you.
• iMessages that can’t be delivered may be held by Apple for up to 30 days for redelivery.
• Apple may record and store information about FaceTime calls, such as who was invited to a call, and your device’s network configurations, and store this information for up to 30 days. Apple doesn’t log whether your call was answered, and can’t access the content of your calls.
• Some apps on your device (including Messages and FaceTime) may communicate with Apple’s servers to determine if other people can be reached by iMessage or FaceTime. When this happens, Apple may store these phone numbers and email addresses associated with your account, for up to 30 days.

By using these features, you agree and consent to Apple’s and its subsidiaries’ and agents’ transmission, collection, maintenance, processing, and use of this information as described above.

Information collected by Apple will be treated in accordance with Apple’s Privacy Policy, which can be found at www.apple.com/privacy</base>
        <tran loc="zh-TW">iMessage是一項Apple提供的服務，可透過WLAN或行動網路連線傳送訊息到其他iOS裝置（iOS 5或以上版本）、iPadOS裝置、Mac電腦（OS X 10.8或以上版本）和Apple Watch上。這些訊息並不會佔用您的簡訊用量。iMessage傳送的訊息可包含照片、影片和其他資訊。

FaceTime是一項Apple提供的服務，可以撥打視訊或語音通話給其他使用iOS或iPadOS裝置或Mac的使用者，或使用Apple Watch撥打語音通話。這些通話並不會佔用您的行動數據時數。

我們設計iMessage和FaceTime使用端對端加密，您的對話內容在裝置間傳輸時，Apple無法解密對話內容。您透過iMessage傳送的附件（例如照片或影片）會進行加密，只有傳送者和接收者才能取用。這些加密的附件可能會傳送到Apple。為增進效能，您的裝置可能會在您編寫iMessage時自動上傳附件到Apple。若您的訊息未送出，附件會在30天後從伺服器上刪除。若您的iOS、iPadOS或watchOS裝置上設定了密碼或通行碼，儲存的訊息會在裝置上加密，除非解鎖裝置才能取用訊息。

您可以選擇在30天或一年之後自動刪除iMessage訊息，或是在裝置上永久保存訊息。若您啟用了「iCloud備份」或「iCloud雲端訊息」，為了方便起見，iMessage訊息會在iCloud上備份並進行加密。您可以隨時關閉「iCloud備份」或「iCloud雲端訊息」。在iOS或iPadOS上，請前往「設定」&gt; [您的名稱] &gt; iCloud。在macOS上，請選擇「訊息」&gt;「偏好設定」，按下iMessage，並且關閉「啟用iCloud雲端訊息」。我們永遠不會儲存FaceTime通話的內容。

您可以使用您的Apple ID或電話號碼來登入iMessage和FaceTime。若您在裝置上登入您的Apple ID，即會自動將您登入iMessage和FaceTime。您的Apple ID和電話號碼會顯示給您的聯絡對象，其他人可以使用您的Apple ID和您帳號的電子郵件位址或電話號碼來聯絡您。您可以在iMessage和FaceTime設定中選取要開始新對話的電話號碼或電子郵件位址，以及可以用來接收和回覆訊息的電話號碼或電子郵件位址。您可以在Apple ID帳號頁面的「與我聯絡」中加入和驗證其他資訊。

「分享姓名和照片」能讓您與iMessage的聊天對象分享姓名和照片。您可以選擇只要自動與您的聯絡人分享，或是每次提示您。您共享的姓名和照片會在下一則iMessage中傳送給您的共享對象，並儲存在他們的裝置上。若您使用iMessage對話與多人共享姓名和照片，您的姓名和照片將會傳送給對話中的所有人。您可以隨時更新您的姓名和照片。若您是自動分享，則會再您下次傳送iMessage給每位分享對象時傳送更新的內容。若您已經分享您的姓名和照片並在稍後關閉分享，其他先前曾經接收您的姓名和照片的人仍會在他們的裝置上擁有您的資訊。您選擇在訊息中使用的姓名和照片會傳送到Apple，並以Apple無法看見的方式進行加密，儲存在Apple的伺服器上。

Apple會記錄並儲存部分與您使用iMessage和FaceTime相關的資訊，以利作業並改進Apple的產品和服務：

• 當您使用iMessage和FaceTime時，Apple會以無法識別您個人身分的方式來儲存您使用服務時的資訊。
• Apple可能會保留無法傳送的iMessage最長達30天，以便重新傳送。
• Apple可能會記錄和儲存FaceTime通話的相關資訊（例如邀請加入通話的對象，以及您裝置的網路設定），並且保留這些資訊最長達30天。Apple不會記錄您的通話是否有人應答，且Apple無法取用通話的內容。
• 您裝置上的部分App（包含「訊息」和FaceTime）可能會與Apple的伺服器通訊，以確定iMessage或FaceTime是否能聯絡到其他人。在此情況下，Apple可能會儲存這些與您帳號相關的電話號碼和電子郵件位址，最長達30天。

使用這些功能，即表示同意並接受Apple及其子公司和代理以如上所示的方式傳送、收集、維護、處理和使用此資訊。

Apple所收集的資訊均會依照「Apple隱私權政策」處理，請參訪：www.apple.com/tw/privacy</tran>
      </TranslationSet>
    </TextItem>
    <TextItem>
      <Description/>
      <Position>SPLASH_SUMMARY</Position>
      <TranslationSet>
        <base loc="en">iMessage and FaceTime are designed to protect your information and enable you to choose what you share.</base>
        <tran loc="zh-TW">iMessage和FaceTime的設計可保護您的資訊並讓您選擇分享的內容。</tran>
      </TranslationSet>
    </TextItem>
    <TextItem>
      <Description/>
      <Position>SPLASH_TITLE</Position>
      <TranslationSet>
        <base loc="en">iMessage and FaceTime &amp; Privacy</base>
        <tran loc="zh-TW">iMessage和FaceTime與隱私權</tran>
      </TranslationSet>
    </TextItem>
    <TextItem>
      <Description/>
      <Position>BUTTON_TITLE</Position>
      <TranslationSet>
        <base loc="en">See how your data is managed…</base>
        <tran loc="zh-TW">查看您資料的管理方式⋯</tran>
      </TranslationSet>
    </TextItem>
    <TextItem>
      <Description/>
      <Position>FOOTER_TEXT_WIFI</Position>
      <TranslationSet>
        <base loc="en">iMessage is an Apple service that sends messages over Wi-Fi or cellular connections to other iOS devices (with iOS 5 or later), iPadOS devices, Mac computers (with OS X 10.8 or later), and Apple Watches. These messages don’t count against your messaging plan. Messages sent via iMessage can include photos, videos, and other info.

FaceTime is an Apple service that makes video or audio calls to someone who’s also using an iOS or iPadOS device or a Mac, or audio calls using an Apple Watch. These calls don’t count against your cellular minutes.

We designed iMessage and FaceTime to use end-to-end encryption, so there’s no way for Apple to decrypt the content of your conversations when they are in transit between devices. Attachments you send over iMessage (such as photos or videos) are encrypted so that no one but the sender and receiver(s) can access them. These encrypted attachments may be uploaded to Apple. To improve performance, your device may automatically upload attachments to Apple while you are composing an iMessage. If your message isn’t sent, the attachments are deleted from the server after 30 days. When a passcode or password is set on your iOS, iPadOS, or watchOS device, stored messages are encrypted on your device so that they can’t be accessed unless the device has been unlocked.

You can choose to automatically delete your iMessages from your device after 30 days or a year, or to keep them on your device forever. For your convenience, iMessages are backed up in iCloud and encrypted if you have either iCloud Backup or Messages in iCloud enabled. You can turn off both iCloud Backup and Messages in iCloud whenever you want. On iOS or iPadOS, go to Settings &gt; [your name] &gt; iCloud. On macOS, choose Messages &gt; Preferences, tap iMessage, and deselect the “Enable Messages in iCloud” checkbox. We never store the content of FaceTime calls.

You can sign in to iMessage and FaceTime using your Apple ID, or just your phone number. If you sign in with your Apple ID on your device, you will be signed in to iMessage and FaceTime automatically. Your Apple ID or phone numbers will be shown to the people you contact, and people can reach you using your Apple ID and email addresses or phone numbers on your account. You can select which phone numbers or email addresses you’d like to start new conversations from, and which phone numbers or email addresses you can receive messages and reply from, in iMessage and FaceTime settings. You can add and verify additional “Reachable At” information from your Apple ID account page.

Share Name and Photo allows you to share a name and photo with people you iMessage. You can choose to automatically share with just your contacts, or to be prompted each time. Your shared name and photo will be sent with your next iMessage to the people you share with, and stored on their devices. If you share your name and photo with an iMessage conversation with multiple people, your name and photo will be sent to all the people in the conversation. You can update your name and photo at any time. If you automatically share, updates will be sent when you next send an iMessage to each person you share with. If you have shared your name and photo and later turn off sharing, others who previously received your name and photo may still have your information on their devices. The name and photo you select for messages will be sent to Apple, and stored on Apple’s servers encrypted in a way that Apple cannot see.

Apple may record and store some information related to your use of iMessage and FaceTime to operate and improve Apple’s products and services:

• When you use iMessage and FaceTime, Apple may store information about your use of the services in a way that doesn’t identify you.
• iMessages that can’t be delivered may be held by Apple for up to 30 days for redelivery.
• Apple may record and store information about FaceTime calls, such as who was invited to a call, and your device’s network configurations, and store this information for up to 30 days. Apple doesn’t log whether your call was answered, and can’t access the content of your calls.
• Some apps on your device (including Messages and FaceTime) may communicate with Apple’s servers to determine if other people can be reached by iMessage or FaceTime. When this happens, Apple may store these phone numbers and email addresses associated with your account, for up to 30 days.

By using these features, you agree and consent to Apple’s and its subsidiaries’ and agents’ transmission, collection, maintenance, processing, and use of this information as described above.

Information collected by Apple will be treated in accordance with Apple’s Privacy Policy, which can be found at www.apple.com/privacy</base>
        <tran loc="zh-TW">iMessage是一項Apple提供的服務，可透過Wi-Fi或行動網路連線傳送訊息到其他iOS裝置（iOS 5或以上版本）、iPadOS裝置、Mac電腦（OS X 10.8或以上版本）和Apple Watch上。這些訊息並不會佔用您的簡訊用量。iMessage傳送的訊息可包含照片、影片和其他資訊。

FaceTime是一項Apple提供的服務，可以撥打視訊或語音通話給其他使用iOS或iPadOS裝置或Mac的使用者，或使用Apple Watch撥打語音通話。這些通話並不會佔用您的行動數據時數。

我們設計iMessage和FaceTime使用端對端加密，您的對話內容在裝置間傳輸時，Apple無法解密對話內容。您透過iMessage傳送的附件（例如照片或影片）會進行加密，只有傳送者和接收者才能取用。這些加密的附件可能會傳送到Apple。為增進效能，您的裝置可能會在您編寫iMessage時自動上傳附件到Apple。若您的訊息未送出，附件會在30天後從伺服器上刪除。若您的iOS、iPadOS或watchOS裝置上設定了密碼或通行碼，儲存的訊息會在裝置上加密，除非解鎖裝置才能取用訊息。

您可以選擇在30天或一年之後自動刪除iMessage訊息，或是在裝置上永久保存訊息。若您啟用了「iCloud備份」或「iCloud雲端訊息」，為了方便起見，iMessage訊息會在iCloud上備份並進行加密。您可以隨時關閉「iCloud備份」或「iCloud雲端訊息」。在iOS或iPadOS上，請前往「設定」&gt; [您的名稱] &gt; iCloud。在macOS上，請選擇「訊息」&gt;「偏好設定」，按下iMessage，然後取消選取「啟用iCloud雲端訊息」註記框。我們永遠不會儲存FaceTime通話的內容。

您可以使用您的Apple ID或電話號碼來登入iMessage和FaceTime。若您在裝置上登入您的Apple ID，即會自動將您登入iMessage和FaceTime。您的Apple ID和電話號碼會顯示給您的聯絡對象，其他人可以使用您的Apple ID和您帳號的電子郵件位址或電話號碼來聯絡您。您可以在iMessage和FaceTime設定中選取要開始新對話的電話號碼或電子郵件位址，以及可以用來接收和回覆訊息的電話號碼或電子郵件位址。您可以在Apple ID帳號頁面的「與我聯絡」中加入和驗證其他資訊。

「分享姓名和照片」能讓您與iMessage的聊天對象分享姓名和照片。您可以選擇只要自動與您的聯絡人分享，或是每次提示您。您共享的姓名和照片會在下一則iMessage中傳送給您的共享對象，並儲存在他們的裝置上。若您使用iMessage對話與多人共享姓名和照片，您的姓名和照片將會傳送給對話中的所有人。您可以隨時更新您的姓名和照片。若您是自動分享，則會再您下次傳送iMessage給每位分享對象時傳送更新的內容。若您已經分享您的姓名和照片並在稍後關閉分享，其他先前曾經接收您的姓名和照片的人仍會在他們的裝置上擁有您的資訊。您選擇在訊息中使用的姓名和照片會傳送到Apple，並以Apple無法看見的方式進行加密，儲存在Apple的伺服器上。

Apple會記錄並儲存部分與您使用iMessage和FaceTime相關的資訊，以利作業並改進Apple的產品和服務：

• 當您使用iMessage和FaceTime時，Apple會以無法識別您個人身分的方式來儲存您使用服務時的資訊。
• Apple可能會保留無法傳送的iMessage最長達30天，以便重新傳送。
• Apple可能會記錄和儲存FaceTime通話的相關資訊（例如邀請加入通話的對象，以及您裝置的網路設定），並且保留這些資訊最長達30天。Apple不會記錄您的通話是否有人應答，且Apple無法取用通話的內容。
• 您裝置上的部分App（包含「訊息」和FaceTime）可能會與Apple的伺服器通訊，以確定iMessage或FaceTime是否能聯絡到其他人。在此情況下，Apple可能會儲存這些與您帳號相關的電話號碼和電子郵件位址，最長達30天。

使用這些功能，即表示同意並接受Apple及其子公司和代理以如上所示的方式傳送、收集、維護、處理和使用此資訊。

Apple所收集的資訊均會依照「Apple隱私權政策」處理，請參訪：www.apple.com/tw/privacy</tran>
      </TranslationSet>
    </TextItem>
